// Semantic direction:
// service_mesh intercepts all inbound and outbound traffic through a sidecar_proxy on each node.
// data_plane is the set of sidecar_proxies executing traffic policy decisions.
// control_plane distributes mesh_config and traffic_policy to all sidecar_proxies.
// service_discovery allows services to find each other by name without hardcoded addresses.
// service_registry is the authoritative store of healthy service_entries.
// register_service adds an endpoint_address and endpoint_port when a service starts.
// dns_discovery returns endpoint addresses via SRV records; dns_ttl controls cache lifetime.
// watch_services notifies clients of service_change_events (added, removed, updated) in real time.
// mTLS (mutual TLS) authenticates both sides of every service-to-service connection.
// spiffe_id is the workload_identity URI (spiffe://trust-domain/service) embedded in the certificate.
// cert_rotation transparently replaces certificates before cert_expiry.
// route_rule directs traffic matching route_match conditions to specific route_destinations.
// traffic_split distributes requests proportionally across dest_subsets by dest_weight.
// canary_route sends a fraction of traffic to the canary version while the rest goes to stable.
// mirror_traffic duplicates requests to a shadow service for testing without affecting users.
// retry_policy automatically resends failed requests up to retry_attempts times with retry_backoff.
// retry_perturb adds jitter to backoff delays to prevent thundering-herd retries.
// outlier_detection removes unhealthy endpoints from the lb pool after consecutive_errors.
// ejection_interval is the minimum time between ejection checks; base_ejection_time grows per ejection.
// max_ejection_percent limits how many endpoints can be ejected simultaneously.
// access_log records every proxied request for audit and debugging.

// Primitive flow:
// service start: sidecar_proxy started alongside app -> register_service(name, addr, port)
// incoming request: sidecar intercepts -> mTLS handshake -> extract spiffe_id
//   -> route_rule match -> traffic_split -> forward to destination
//   -> retry_policy: on error retry up to retry_attempts with backoff
//   -> timeout_policy: request_timeout exceeded -> abort + return 503
// outlier_detection: consecutive_errors > threshold -> eject endpoint
//   -> base_ejection_time * (ejection count) -> re-add after cooldown
// canary_route: 5% of requests -> canary dest_subset, 95% -> stable
// mirror_traffic: copy request to shadow service (response discarded)
// access_log + mesh_metric + mesh_trace: sidecar emits per request

// This defines service mesh architecture, mTLS workload identity, traffic routing,
// retries, timeouts, outlier detection, and service discovery.
